  "prompt": "What pre-action would you take in case of earthquakes?",
  "response": "Here are some pre-action steps for earthquake preparedness:\n\n1. Home Preparation\n- Secure heavy furniture to walls\n- Install latches on cabinets\n- Secure water heater and large appliances\n- Identify safe spots in each room (under sturdy tables)\n\n2. Emergency Kit\n- Store water (1 gallon per person per day)\n- Non-perishable food\n- First aid kit\n- Flashlights and extra batteries\n- Battery-powered radio\n- Prescription medications\n- Cash\n- Important documents\n\n3. Family Planning\n- Create an emergency communication plan\n- Designate an out-of-area contact\n- Teach family members basic earthquake safety\n- Know evacuation routes\n- Establish meeting points\n\n4. Home Structural Assessment\n- Check building's earthquake resistance\n- Reinforce foundation if necessary\n- Consult structural engineers\n- Consider retrofitting\n\n5. Insurance\n- Review homeowner's/renter's insurance\n- Consider earthquake insurance\n- Understand coverage details\n\n6. Community Awareness\n- Learn local earthquake protocols\n- Know community emergency centers\n- Participate in earthquake drills\n\n7. Personal Skills\n- Learn first aid\n- Take emergency response classes\n- Know how to shut off utilities\n\nThese steps can help minimize risks during an earthquake.",
